# TRIGGER
- a stored program in MySQL that runs automatically when a specific event(INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) happens on a table 
- unlike stored procedures, you don't call triggers manually(they fire on their own)
- use
# Types
 i. BEOFRE triggers
 - runs before the event executes. 
 - useful for validation or modifying values before saving.
 ii. AFTER triggers
 - runs after the event executes.
 - useful for logging, auditing, or syncing data
Syntax:
    CREATE TRIGGER trigger_NAME
   {BEFORE | AFTER} {INSERT | UPDATE | DELETE} ON table_name 
   FOR EACH ROW 
   BEGIN
   -- SQL statements
   END;